48 //this could be a variadic template function; directly use pt_frob_error() for formatted messages without catalog
49 #define pt_cat_error(parser, node, setNo, msgNo, ...) \
50  pt_frob_error(parser, node, msgcat_message(MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, setNo, msgNo), ##__VA_ARGS__)

59 #define PT_ERRORf4(parser, node, msg, arg1, arg2, arg3, arg4) pt_frob_error(parser, node, msg, arg1, arg2, arg3, arg4)
60 #define PT_ERRORf5(parser, node, msg, arg1, arg2, arg3, arg4, arg5) pt_frob_error(parser, node, msg, arg1, arg2, arg3, arg4, arg5)

88 #define PT_SET_JMP_ENV(parser) \
89  do { \
90  if (setjmp((parser)->jmp_env) != 0) { \
91  pt_record_error((parser), (parser)->statement_number, \
92  (parser)->line, \
93  (parser)->column, \
94  msgcat_message (MSGCAT_CATALOG_CUBRID, \
95  MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, \
96  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY), \
97  NULL); \
98  (parser)->jmp_env_active = 0; \
99  if ((parser)->au_save) \
100  AU_ENABLE((parser)->au_save); \
101  return NULL; \
102  } \
103  else (parser)->jmp_env_active = 1; \
104  } while(0)
105 
106 #define PT_CLEAR_JMP_ENV(parser) \
107  do { \
108  (parser)->jmp_env_active = 0; \
109  } while(0)

111 #define PT_INTERNAL_ERROR(parser, what) \
112  pt_internal_error((parser), __FILE__, __LINE__, (what))

114 #define PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE(x) \
115  ( (x) == PT_SELECT || (x) == PT_UNION \
116  || (x) == PT_DIFFERENCE || (x) == PT_INTERSECTION)
117 
118 #define PT_IS_CLASSOID_NAME(x) \
119  ( (x)->info.name.meta_class == PT_CLASSOID_ATTR)
120 
121 #define PT_IS_NULL_NODE(e) ((e)->type_enum==PT_TYPE_NA \
122  || (e)->type_enum==PT_TYPE_NULL)
123 
124 #define PT_IS_NUMERIC_TYPE(t) \
125  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_INTEGER) || \
126  ((t) == PT_TYPE_BIGINT) || \
127  ((t) == PT_TYPE_FLOAT) || \
128  ((t) == PT_TYPE_DOUBLE) || \
129  ((t) == PT_TYPE_SMALLINT) || \
130  ((t) == PT_TYPE_MONETARY) || \
131  ((t) == PT_TYPE_LOGICAL) || \
132  ((t) == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC)) ? true : false )
133 
134 #define PT_IS_DISCRETE_NUMBER_TYPE(t) \
135  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_INTEGER) || \
136  ((t) == PT_TYPE_BIGINT) || \
137  ((t) == PT_TYPE_SMALLINT)) ? true : false )
138 
139 #define PT_IS_COUNTER_TYPE(t) \
140  PT_IS_DISCRETE_NUMBER_TYPE(t)
141 
142 #define PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE(t) \
143  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_SET) || \
144  ((t) == PT_TYPE_MULTISET) || \
145  ((t) == PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE)) ? true : false )
146 
147 #define PT_IS_STRING_TYPE(t) \
148  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_CHAR) || \
149  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARCHAR) || \
150  ((t) == PT_TYPE_NCHAR) || \
151  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR) || \
152  ((t) == PT_TYPE_BIT) || \
153  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARBIT)) ? true : false )
154 
155 #define PT_IS_NATIONAL_CHAR_STRING_TYPE(t) \
156  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_NCHAR) || \
157  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR)) ? true : false )
158 
159 #define PT_IS_SIMPLE_CHAR_STRING_TYPE(t) \
160  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_CHAR) || \
161  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARCHAR)) ? true : false )
162 
163 #define PT_IS_CHAR_STRING_TYPE(t) \
164  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_CHAR) || \
165  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARCHAR) || \
166  ((t) == PT_TYPE_NCHAR) || \
167  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR)) ? true : false )
168 
169 #define PT_IS_BIT_STRING_TYPE(t) \
170  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_BIT) || \
171  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARBIT)) ? true : false )
172 
173 #define PT_IS_COMPLEX_TYPE(t) \
174  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_MONETARY) || \
175  ((t) == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC) || \
176  ((t) == PT_TYPE_CHAR) || \
177  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARCHAR) || \
178  ((t) == PT_TYPE_NCHAR) || \
179  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR) || \
180  ((t) == PT_TYPE_BIT) || \
181  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARBIT) || \
182  ((t) == PT_TYPE_OBJECT) || \
183  ((t) == PT_TYPE_SET) || \
184  ((t) == PT_TYPE_MULTISET) || \
185  ((t) == PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE) || \
186  ((t) == PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION)) ? true : false )
187 
188 #define PT_IS_DATE_TIME_WITH_TZ_TYPE(t) \
189  ( ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ || \
190  (t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ || \
191  (t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ || \
192  (t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ) ? true : false )
193 
194 #define PT_IS_DATE_TIME_TYPE(t) \
195  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_DATE) || \
196  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIME) || \
197  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMP) || \
198  ((t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIME) || \
199  ((t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ) || \
200  ((t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ) || \
201  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ) || \
202  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ)) ? true : false )
203 
204 #define PT_HAS_DATE_PART(t) \
205  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_DATE) || \
206  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMP) || \
207  ((t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIME) || \
208  ((t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ) || \
209  ((t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ) || \
210  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ) || \
211  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ)) ? true : false )
212 
213 #define PT_HAS_TIME_PART(t) \
214  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_TIME) || \
215  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMP) || \
216  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ) || \
217  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ) || \
218  ((t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIME) || \
219  ((t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ) || \
220  ((t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ)) ? true : false )
221 
222 #define PT_IS_LTZ_TYPE(t) \
223  ((t) == PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ || (t) == PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ)
224 
225 #define PT_IS_PRIMITIVE_TYPE(t) \
226  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_OBJECT) || \
227  ((t) == PT_TYPE_NONE)) ? false : true )
228 
229 #define PT_IS_PARAMETERIZED_TYPE(t) \
230  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC) || \
231  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARCHAR) || \
232  ((t) == PT_TYPE_CHAR) || \
233  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR) || \
234  ((t) == PT_TYPE_NCHAR) || \
235  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARBIT) || \
236  ((t) == PT_TYPE_BIT) || \
237  ((t) == PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION)) ? true : false )
238 
239 #define PT_IS_LOB_TYPE(t) \
240  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_BLOB) || \
241  ((t) == PT_TYPE_CLOB)) ? true : false )
242 
243 #define PT_HAS_COLLATION(t) \
244  ( (((t) == PT_TYPE_CHAR) || \
245  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARCHAR) || \
246  ((t) == PT_TYPE_NCHAR) || \
247  ((t) == PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR) || \
248  ((t) == PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION)) ? true : false )

250 #define PT_VALUE_GET_BYTES(node) \
251  ((node) == NULL ? NULL : \

257 #define pt_is_difference(n) PT_IS_DIFFERENCE(n)
258 #define pt_is_query(n) PT_IS_QUERY(n)
259 #define pt_is_correlated_subquery(n) PT_IS_CORRELATED_SUBQUERY(n)
260 #define pt_is_dot_node(n) PT_IS_DOT_NODE(n)
261 #define pt_is_expr_node(n) PT_IS_EXPR_NODE(n)
262 #define pt_is_function(n) PT_IS_FUNCTION(n)

272 #define pt_is_input_parameter(n) PT_IS_INPUT_PARAMETER(n)

283 #define PT_IS_SELECT(n) \
284  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_SELECT) : false )
285 
286 #define PT_IS_UNION(n) \
287  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_UNION) : false )
288 
289 #define PT_IS_INTERSECTION(n) \
290  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_INTERSECTION) : false )
291 
292 #define PT_IS_DIFFERENCE(n) \
293  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_DIFFERENCE) : false )
294 
295 #define PT_IS_QUERY(n) \
296  ( (n) ? (PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE((n)->node_type)) : false )
297 
298 #define PT_IS_CORRELATED_SUBQUERY(n) \
299  ( (PT_IS_QUERY((n)) && (n)->info.query.correlation_level > 0) ? \
300  true : false )
301 
302 #define PT_IS_DOT_NODE(n) \
303  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_DOT_) : false )
304 
305 #define PT_IS_EXPR_NODE(n) \
306  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_EXPR) : false )
307 
308 #define PT_IS_ASSIGN_NODE(n) \
309  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_EXPR && \
310  (n)->info.expr.op == PT_ASSIGN) \
311  : false )
312 
313 #define PT_IS_FUNCTION(n) \
314  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_FUNCTION) : false )
315 
316 #define PT_IS_NAME_NODE(n) \
317  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_NAME) : false )
318 
319 #define PT_IS_OID_NAME(n) \
320  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_NAME && \
321  ((n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_OID_ATTR || \
322  (n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_VID_ATTR)) \
323  : false )
324 
325 #define PT_IS_VALUE_NODE(n) \
326  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_VALUE) : false )
327 
328 #define PT_IS_INSERT_VALUE_NODE(n) \
329  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_INSERT_VALUE) : false )
330 
331 #define PT_IS_SET_TYPE(n) \
332  ( (n) ? ((n)->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SET || \
333  (n)->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MULTISET || \
334  (n)->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE) \
335  : false )
336 
337 #define PT_IS_HOSTVAR(n) \
338  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR) : false )
339 
340 #define PT_IS_INPUT_HOSTVAR(n) \
341  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR && \
342  (n)->info.host_var.var_type == PT_HOST_IN) \
343  : false )
344 
345 #define PT_IS_OUTPUT_HOSTVAR(n) \
346  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR && \
347  (n)->info.host_var.var_type == PT_HOST_OUT) \
348  : false )
349 
350 #define PT_IS_PARAMETER(n) \
351  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_NAME && \
352  (n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER) : false )
353 
354 #define PT_IS_INPUT_PARAMETER(n) \
355  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_NAME && \
356  (n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER && \
357  (n)->info.name.resolved == NULL) : false )
358 
359 #define PT_IS_CONST(n) \
360  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_VALUE || \
361  (n)->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR || \
362  ((n)->node_type == PT_NAME && \
363  (n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER)) \
364  : false )
365 
366 #define PT_IS_CONST_NOT_HOSTVAR(n) \
367  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_VALUE || \
368  ((n)->node_type == PT_NAME && \
369  (n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER)) \
370  : false )
371 
372 #define PT_IS_CONST_INPUT_HOSTVAR(n) \
373  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_VALUE || \
374  ((n)->node_type == PT_NAME && \
375  (n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER) || \
376  ((n)->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR && \
377  (n)->info.host_var.var_type == PT_HOST_IN)) \
378  : false )
379 
380 #define PT_IS_CAST_CONST_INPUT_HOSTVAR(n) \
381  ( (n) && \
382  (n)->node_type == PT_EXPR && \
383  (n)->info.expr.op == PT_CAST \
384  ? PT_IS_CONST_INPUT_HOSTVAR((n)->info.expr.arg1) \
385  : false )
386 
387 #define PT_IS_INSTNUM(n) \
388  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_EXPR && \
389  ((n)->info.expr.op == PT_INST_NUM || \
390  (n)->info.expr.op == PT_ROWNUM)) \
391  : false )
392 
393 #define PT_IS_ORDERBYNUM(n) \
394  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_EXPR && \
395  ((n)->info.expr.op == PT_ORDERBY_NUM)) \
396  : false )
397 
398 #define PT_IS_DISTINCT(n) \
399  ( ((n) && PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE((n)->node_type) ? \
400  (n)->info.query.all_distinct != PT_ALL : false) )
401 
402 #define PT_IS_META(n) \
403  ( ((n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_NAME ? \
404  ((n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS || \
405  (n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_ATTR || \
406  (n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_CLASSOID_ATTR || \
407  (n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_OID_ATTR) : \
408  ((n)->node_type == PT_SPEC ? \
409  ((n)->info.spec.meta_class == PT_META_CLASS) : false)) \
410  : false) )
411 #define PT_IS_HINT_NODE(n) \
412  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_NAME && \
413  (n)->info.name.meta_class == PT_HINT_NAME) \
414  : false )
415 
416 #define PT_IS_UPDATE_OBJECT(n) \
417  ( ((n) && \
418  (n)->node_type == PT_UPDATE && \
419  (n)->info.update.spec == NULL) ? true : false )
420 
421 #define PT_IS_UNARY(op) \
422  ( ((op) == PT_NOT || \
423  (op) == PT_IS_NULL || \
424  (op) == PT_IS_NOT_NULL || \
425  (op) == PT_EXISTS || \
426  (op) == PT_PRIOR || \
427  (op) == PT_CONNECT_BY_ROOT || \
428  (op) == PT_QPRIOR || \
429  (op) == PT_UNARY_MINUS) ? true : false )
430 
431 #define PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR(n) \
432  ( ((n) && \
433  (n)->node_type == PT_EXPR && \
434  (n)->info.expr.op == PT_PATH_EXPR_SET) ? true : false )
435 
436 #define PT_DOES_FUNCTION_HAVE_DIFFERENT_ARGS(op) \
437  ((op) == PT_MODULUS || (op) == PT_SUBSTRING || \
438  (op) == PT_LPAD || (op) == PT_RPAD || (op) == PT_ADD_MONTHS || \
439  (op) == PT_TO_CHAR || (op) == PT_TO_NUMBER || \
440  (op) == PT_POWER || (op) == PT_ROUND || \
441  (op) == PT_TRUNC || (op) == PT_INSTR || \
442  (op) == PT_LEAST || (op) == PT_GREATEST || \
443  (op) == PT_FIELD || \
444  (op) == PT_REPEAT || (op) == PT_SUBSTRING_INDEX || \
445  (op) == PT_MAKEDATE || (op) == PT_MAKETIME || (op) == PT_IF || \
446  (op) == PT_STR_TO_DATE)
447 
448 #define PT_REQUIRES_HIERARCHICAL_QUERY(op) \
449  ( ((op) == PT_LEVEL || \
450  (op) == PT_CONNECT_BY_ISCYCLE || \
451  (op) == PT_CONNECT_BY_ISLEAF || \
452  (op) == PT_PRIOR || \
453  (op) == PT_CONNECT_BY_ROOT || \
454  (op) == PT_QPRIOR || \
455  (op) == PT_SYS_CONNECT_BY_PATH) ? true : false )
456 
457 #define PT_IS_NUMBERING_AFTER_EXECUTION(op) \
458  ( ((op) == PT_INST_NUM || \
459  (op) == PT_ROWNUM || \
460  /*(int)(op) == (int)PT_GROUPBY_NUM || - TODO: this does not belong here. */ \
461  (op) == PT_ORDERBY_NUM) ? true : false )
462 
463 #define PT_IS_SERIAL(op) \
464  ( ((op) == PT_CURRENT_VALUE || \
465  (op) == PT_NEXT_VALUE) ? true : false )
466 
467 #define PT_IS_EXPR_NODE_WITH_OPERATOR(n, op_type) \
468  ( (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (n)) ? ((n)->info.expr.op == (op_type)) : false )
469 
470 #define PT_IS_EXPR_WITH_PRIOR_ARG(x) (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (x) && \
471  PT_IS_EXPR_NODE_WITH_OPERATOR ((x)->info.expr.arg1, PT_PRIOR))
472 
473 #define PT_NODE_DATA_TYPE(n) \
474  ( (n) ? (n)->data_type : NULL )
475 
476 #define PT_IS_SORT_SPEC_NODE(n) \
477  ( (n) ? ((n)->node_type == PT_SORT_SPEC) : false )
478 
479 #define PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY(n) \
480  ((n)->is_value_query == 1)
481 
482 #define PT_SET_VALUE_QUERY(n) \
483  ((n)->is_value_query = 1)
484 
485 #define PT_IS_ORDER_DEPENDENT(n) \
486  ( (n) ? \
487  (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (n) ? (n)->info.expr.is_order_dependent \
488  : (PT_IS_FUNCTION(n) ? (n)->info.function.is_order_dependent \
489  : (PT_IS_QUERY(n) ? (n)->info.query.is_order_dependent : false))) \
490  : false)
491 
492 #define PT_IS_ANALYTIC_NODE(n) \
493  ( (n) && (n)->node_type == PT_FUNCTION && \
494  (n)->info.function.analytic.is_analytic )
495 
496 #define PT_IS_POINTER_REF_NODE(n) \
497  ( (n) && (n)->node_type == PT_NODE_POINTER && \
498  (n)->info.pointer.type == PT_POINTER_REF )
499 
500 #define PT_IS_VACUUM_NODE(n) \
501  ( (n) && (n)->node_type == PT_VACUUM )
502 
503 #define PT_SET_ORDER_DEPENDENT_FLAG(n, f) \
504  do { \
505  if ((n)) \
506  { \
507  if (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (n)) \
508  (n)->info.expr.is_order_dependent = (f); \
509  else if (PT_IS_FUNCTION (n)) \
510  (n)->info.function.is_order_dependent = (f); \
511  else if (PT_IS_QUERY (n)) \
512  (n)->info.query.is_order_dependent = (f); \
513  } \
514  } while (0)
515 
516 #if !defined (SERVER_MODE)
517 /* the following defines support host variable binding for internal statements.
518  internal statements can be generated on TEXT handling, and these statements
519  can include host variables derived from original statement. so, to look up
520  host variable table by internal statements at parser, keep the parser,
521  i.e parent_parser */
522 
523 #define CLEAR_HOST_VARIABLES(parser_) \
524  do { DB_VALUE *hv; int i; \
525  for (i = 0, hv = parser_->host_variables; \
526  i < (parser_->host_var_count + parser_->auto_param_count); i++, hv++) \
527  db_value_clear(hv); \
528  free_and_init(parser_->host_variables); \
529  free_and_init(parser_->host_var_expected_domains);} while (0)
530 
531 #define SET_HOST_VARIABLES_IF_INTERNAL_STATEMENT(parser_) \
532  do { if (parent_parser) { \
533  if (parser_->host_variables != NULL && \
534  parser_->host_variables != parent_parser->host_variables) { \
535  CLEAR_HOST_VARIABLES(parser_); } \
536  parser_->host_variables = parent_parser->host_variables; \
537  parser_->host_var_expected_domains = parent_parser->host_var_expected_domains; \
538  parser_->host_var_count = parent_parser->host_var_count; \
539  parser_->auto_param_count = parent_parser->auto_param_count; \
540  parser_->set_host_var = 1; } } while (0)
541 
542 #define RESET_HOST_VARIABLES_IF_INTERNAL_STATEMENT(parser_) \
543  do { if (parent_parser) { \
544  parser_->host_variables = NULL; parser_->host_var_count = 0; \
545  parser_->host_var_expected_domains = NULL; \
546  parser_->auto_param_count = 0; parser_->set_host_var = 0; } } while (0)
547 
548 #endif /* !SERVER_MODE */

551 /* NODE FUNCTION DECLARATIONS */
552 #define IS_UPDATE_OBJ(node) (node->node_type == PT_UPDATE && node->info.update.object_parameter)
553 
554 #define PT_NODE_INIT_OUTERLINK(n) \
555  do { \
556  if ((n)) { \
557  (n)->next = NULL; \
558  (n)->or_next = NULL; \
559  (n)->etc = NULL; \
560  (n)->alias_print = NULL; \
561  } \
562  } while (0)
563 
564 #define PT_NODE_COPY_NUMBER_OUTERLINK(t, s) \
565  do { \
566  if ((t) && (s)) { \
567  (t)->line_number = (s)->line_number; \
568  (t)->column_number = (s)->column_number; \
569  (t)->next = (s)->next; \
570  (t)->or_next = (s)->or_next; \
571  (t)->etc = (s)->etc; \
572  (t)->alias_print = (s)->alias_print; \
573  } \
574  } while (0)
575 
576 #define PT_NODE_MOVE_NUMBER_OUTERLINK(t, s) \
577  do { \
578  PT_NODE_COPY_NUMBER_OUTERLINK((t), (s)); \
579  PT_NODE_INIT_OUTERLINK((s)); \
580  } while (0)
581 
582 #define PT_NODE_PRINT_TO_ALIAS(p, n, c) \
583  do { \
584  unsigned int save_custom; \
585  \
586  if (!(p) || !(n) || (n->alias_print)) \
587  break; \
588  save_custom = (p)->custom_print; \
589  (p)->custom_print |= (c); \
590  if (((p)->custom_print & PT_SHORT_PRINT) != 0) \
591  { \
592  (n)->alias_print = pt_short_print ((p), (n)); \
593  } \
594  else \
595  { \
596  (n)->alias_print = parser_print_tree ((p), (n)); \
597  } \
598  (p)->custom_print = save_custom; \
599  } while (0)
600 
601 #define PT_NODE_PRINT_VALUE_TO_TEXT(p, n) \
602  do { \
603  if (!(p) || !(n) || (n)->node_type != PT_VALUE \
604  || (n)->info.value.text) \
605  { \
606  break; \
607  } \
608  (n)->info.value.text = parser_print_tree ((p), (n)); \
609  } while (0)
610 
611 #define CAST_POINTER_TO_NODE(p) \
612  do { \
613  while ((p) && (p)->node_type == PT_NODE_POINTER && \
614  (p)->info.pointer.type == PT_POINTER_NORMAL) \
615  { \
616  (p) = (p)->info.pointer.node; \
617  } \
618  } while (0)
619 
620 #define PT_EMPTY INT_MAX
621 #define MAX_NUM_PLAN_TRACE 100
622 
623 #define PT_GET_COLLATION_MODIFIER(p) \
624  (((p)->node_type == PT_EXPR) ? ((p)->info.expr.coll_modifier - 1) : \
625  (((p)->node_type == PT_VALUE) ? ((p)->info.value.coll_modifier - 1) : \
626  (((p)->node_type == PT_NAME) ? ((p)->info.name.coll_modifier - 1) : \
627  (((p)->node_type == PT_FUNCTION) ? ((p)->info.function.coll_modifier - 1) :\
628  (((p)->node_type == PT_DOT_) ? ((p)->info.dot.coll_modifier - 1) : (-1))))))
629 
630 #define PT_SET_NODE_COLL_MODIFIER(p, coll) \
631  do { \
632  assert ((p) != NULL); \
633  if ((p)->node_type == PT_EXPR) \
634  { \
635  (p)->info.expr.coll_modifier = (coll) + 1; \
636  } \
637  else if ((p)->node_type == PT_VALUE) \
638  { \
639  (p)->info.value.coll_modifier = (coll) + 1; \
640  } \
641  else if ((p)->node_type == PT_NAME) \
642  { \
643  (p)->info.name.coll_modifier = (coll) + 1; \
644  } \
645  else if ((p)->node_type == PT_FUNCTION) \
646  { \
647  (p)->info.function.coll_modifier = (coll) + 1; \
648  } \
649  else \
650  { \
651  assert ((p)->node_type == PT_DOT_); \
652  (p)->info.dot.coll_modifier = (coll) + 1; \
653  } \
654  } while (0)
655 
656 /* Check if spec is flagged with any of flags_ */
657 #define PT_IS_SPEC_FLAG_SET(spec_, flags_) \
658  (((spec_)->info.spec.flag & (flags_)) != 0)
659 
660 #define PT_SPEC_SPECIAL_INDEX_SCAN(spec_) \
661  (((spec_)->info.spec.flag & \
662  (PT_SPEC_FLAG_KEY_INFO_SCAN | PT_SPEC_FLAG_BTREE_NODE_INFO_SCAN)) != 0)
663 
664 /* Obtain reserved name type from spec flag */
665 #define PT_SPEC_GET_RESERVED_NAME_TYPE(spec_) \
666  (((spec_) == NULL || (spec_)->node_type != PT_SPEC \
667  || (spec_)->info.spec.flag == 0) ? \
668  /* is spec is NULL or not a PT_SPEC or flag is 0, return invalid */ \
669  RESERVED_NAME_INVALID : \
670  /* else */ \
671  ((PT_IS_SPEC_FLAG_SET (spec_, PT_SPEC_FLAG_RECORD_INFO_SCAN)) ? \
672  /* if spec is flagged for record info */ \
673  RESERVED_NAME_RECORD_INFO : \
674  /* else */ \
675  ((PT_IS_SPEC_FLAG_SET (spec_, PT_SPEC_FLAG_PAGE_INFO_SCAN)) ? \
676  /* if spec is flagged for page info */ \
677  RESERVED_NAME_PAGE_INFO : \
678  /* else */ \
679  ((PT_IS_SPEC_FLAG_SET (spec_, PT_SPEC_FLAG_KEY_INFO_SCAN)) ? \
680  /* if spec is flagged for key info */ \
681  RESERVED_NAME_KEY_INFO : \
682  /* else */ \
683  ((PT_IS_SPEC_FLAG_SET(spec_, PT_SPEC_FLAG_BTREE_NODE_INFO_SCAN) ? \
684  /* if spec is flagged for b-tree node info */ \
685  RESERVED_NAME_BTREE_NODE_INFO : \
686  /* spec is not flagged for any type of reserved names */ \
687  RESERVED_NAME_INVALID))))))
688 
689 /* Check if according to spec flag should bind names as reserved */
690 #define PT_SHOULD_BIND_RESERVED_NAME(spec_) \
691  (PT_SPEC_GET_RESERVED_NAME_TYPE (spec_) != RESERVED_NAME_INVALID)
692 
693 /* PT_SPEC node contains a derived table */
694 #define PT_SPEC_IS_DERIVED(spec_) \
695  ((spec_)->info.spec.derived_table != NULL)
696 
697 /* PT_SPEC node contains a CTE pointer */
698 #define PT_SPEC_IS_CTE(spec_) \
699  ((spec_)->info.spec.cte_pointer != NULL)
700 
701 /* PT_SPEC node contains an entity spec */
702 #define PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY(spec_) \
703  ((spec_)->info.spec.entity_name != NULL)
704 
705 #define PT_IS_FALSE_WHERE_VALUE(node) \
706  (((node) != NULL && (node)->node_type == PT_VALUE \
707  && ((node)->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL \
708  || ((node)->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SET \
709  && ((node)->info.value.data_value.set == NULL)))) ? true : false)
710 
711 #define PT_IS_SPEC_REAL_TABLE(spec_) PT_SPEC_IS_ENTITY(spec_)

713 /*
714  Enumerated types of parse tree statements
715  WARNING ------ WARNING ----- WARNING
716  Member functions parser_new_node, parser_init_node, parser_print_tree, which take a node as an argument
717  are accessed by function tables indexed by node_type. The functions in
718  the tables must appear in EXACTLY the same order as the node types
719  defined below. If you add a new node type you must create the
720  functions to manipulate it and put these in the tables. Else crash and burn.
721 */

1001  * now captured via a first class server function F_CLASS_OF which takes an arbitrary instance valued expression. */
1002  PT_CLASSOID_ATTR,
1003  PT_TRIGGER_OID,

1006  * does not vary as instance OIDs vary across an inheritance hierarchy). Contrast this with the F_CLASS_OF function
1007  * which returns the class OID for any instance valued expression. F_CLASS_OF is a server side function. */

1763 struct pt_alter_info
1764 {
1765  PT_NODE *entity_name; /* PT_NAME */
1766  PT_ALTER_CODE code; /* value will be PT_ADD_ATTR, PT_DROP_ATTR ... */
1767  PT_MISC_TYPE entity_type; /* PT_VCLASS, ... */

1769  {

1771  PT_NODE *resolution_list; /* PT_RESOLUTION */

1775  struct

1777  PT_NODE *query; /* PT_SELECT */

1779  PT_NODE *attr_def_list; /* to be filled in semantic check */
1780  PT_NODE *view_comment; /* PT_VALUE */
1781  } query;

1783  {

1788  PT_NODE *mthd_file_list; /* PT_FILE_PATH */
1789  PT_NODE *mthd_name_list; /* PT_NAME(list) */
1790  PT_MISC_TYPE attr_type; /* PT_NORMAL_ATTR, PT_CLASS_ATTR */
1791  } attr_mthd;
1792  struct
1793  {
1794  PT_NODE *attr_name_list; /* PT_NAME(list) */
1795  PT_NODE *data_default_list; /* PT_DATA_DEFAULT(list) */
1796  } ch_attr_def;
1797  struct
1798  {
1799  PT_MISC_TYPE element_type; /* PT_ATTRIBUTE, PT_METHOD */
1800  PT_MISC_TYPE meta; /* PT_META, PT_NORMAL */

1802  PT_NODE *new_name;

1804  PT_MISC_TYPE mthd_type; /* PT_META, PT_NORMAL */
1805  } rename;

1807  {
1808  PT_NODE *info; /* PT_PARTITION_INFO */
1809  PT_NODE *name_list; /* PT_NAME(list) */
1810  PT_NODE *parts; /* PT_PARTS_INFO(list) */
1811  PT_NODE *size; /* PT_VALUE */
1812  } partition;
1813  struct
1814  {
1815  int charset; /* charset for PT_CHANGE_COLLATION If the alter statement contains a valid charset
1816  * spec, it is saved into the corresponding member of the struct(charset) Otherwise,
1817  * charset = -1. */
1818  int collation_id; /* collation for PT_CHANGE_COLLATION If the alter statement contains a valid collation
1819  * spec, it is saved into the corresponding member of the struct, e.g. collation_id.
1820  * Otherwise, collation_id = -1. */
1821  } collation;
1822  struct
1823  {
1824  bool reverse;
1825  bool unique;
1826  } index;

1833  PT_NODE *user_name; /* user name for PT_CHANGE_OWNER */
1834  } user;
1835  struct
1836  {
1837  PT_NODE *tbl_comment; /* PT_VALUE, comment for table/view */
1838  } comment;
1839  } alter_clause;

1841  PT_NODE *create_index; /* PT_CREATE_INDEX from ALTER ADD INDEX */
1842  PT_NODE *internal_stmts; /* internally created statements to handle TEXT */
1843  PT_HINT_ENUM hint;
1844 };

2236  * rewrite stage of query optimizer */

2239 #endif

2241  * instead of failing */

2479 /* Reserved name info */
2480 typedef struct pt_reserved_name PT_RESERVED_NAME;
2481 struct pt_reserved_name

2487 
2488 /* Global reserved name table which stores info for each name */
2489 extern PT_RESERVED_NAME pt_Reserved_name_table[];
2490 
2491 /* Obtain reserved name type from id */
2492 #define PT_GET_RESERVED_NAME_TYPE(reserved_id) \
2493  (((reserved_id) >= RESERVED_FIRST_RECORD_INFO \
2494  && (reserved_id) <= RESERVED_LAST_RECORD_INFO) ? \
2495  /* If reserved_id belongs to record info */ \
2496  RESERVED_NAME_RECORD_INFO : \
2497  /* else */ \
2498  (((reserved_id) >= RESERVED_FIRST_PAGE_INFO \
2499  && (reserved_id) <= RESERVED_LAST_PAGE_INFO) ? \
2500  /* If reserved_id belongs to page_info */ \
2501  RESERVED_NAME_PAGE_INFO : \
2502  /* else */ \
2503  (((reserved_id) >= RESERVED_FIRST_KEY_INFO \
2504  && (reserved_id) <= RESERVED_LAST_KEY_INFO) ? \
2505  /* If reserved_id belongs to key info */ \
2506  RESERVED_NAME_KEY_INFO : \
2507  /* else */ \
2508  (((reserved_id) >= RESERVED_FIRST_BT_NODE_INFO \
2509  && (reserved_id) <= RESERVED_LAST_BT_NODE_INFO) ? \
2510  /* If reserved_id belongs to b-tree node info */ \
2511  RESERVED_NAME_BTREE_NODE_INFO : \
2512  /* else must be invalid */ \
2513  RESERVED_NAME_INVALID))))
2514 
2515 /* Get first and last id for reserved name type */
2516 #define PT_GET_RESERVED_NAME_FIRST_AND_LAST(type, first, last) \
2517  switch (type) \
2518  { \
2519  case RESERVED_NAME_RECORD_INFO: \
2520  (first) = RESERVED_FIRST_RECORD_INFO; \
2521  (last) = RESERVED_LAST_RECORD_INFO; \
2522  break; \
2523  case RESERVED_NAME_PAGE_INFO: \
2524  (first) = RESERVED_FIRST_PAGE_INFO; \
2525  (last) = RESERVED_LAST_PAGE_INFO; \
2526  break; \
2527  case RESERVED_NAME_KEY_INFO: \
2528  (first) = RESERVED_FIRST_KEY_INFO; \
2529  (last) = RESERVED_LAST_KEY_INFO; \
2530  break; \
2531  case RESERVED_NAME_BTREE_NODE_INFO: \
2532  (first) = RESERVED_FIRST_BT_NODE_INFO; \
2533  (last) = RESERVED_LAST_BT_NODE_INFO; \
2534  break; \
2535  default: \
2536  assert (0); \
2537  break; \
2538  }
2539 
2540 /* After resolving to a reserved name, check the binding is correct according
2541  * to spec flag
2542  */
2543 #define PT_CHECK_RESERVED_NAME_BIND(spec_, reserved_id) \
2544  (PT_SPEC_GET_RESERVED_NAME_TYPE (spec_) \
2545  == PT_GET_RESERVED_NAME_TYPE (reserved_id))

2618 /* PT_IDX_HINT_ORDER is used in index hint rewrite, to sort the index hints
2619  * in the using_index clause in the order implied by this define; this is
2620  * needed in order to avoid additional loops through the hint list */
2621 #define PT_IDX_HINT_ORDER(hint_node) \
2622  ((hint_node->etc == (void *) PT_IDX_HINT_CLASS_NONE) ? 1 : \
2623  (hint_node->etc == (void *) PT_IDX_HINT_IGNORE ? 2 : \
2624  (hint_node->etc == (void *) PT_IDX_HINT_FORCE ? 3 : \
2625  (hint_node->etc == (void *) PT_IDX_HINT_USE ? 4 : 0))))

2729 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_ANSI_JOIN 0x01 /* has ANSI join? */
2730 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_ORACLE_OUTER 0x02 /* has Oracle's outer join operator? */
2731 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_DUMMY 0x04 /* is dummy (i.e., 'SELECT * FROM x') ? */
2732 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_HAS_AGG 0x08 /* has any type of aggregation? */
2733 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_HAS_ANALYTIC 0x10 /* has analytic functions */
2734 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_MULTI_UPDATE_AGG 0x20 /* is query for multi-table update using aggregate */
2735 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_IDX_SCHEMA 0x40 /* is show index query */
2736 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_COLS_SCHEMA 0x80 /* is show columns query */
2737 #define PT_SELECT_FULL_INFO_COLS_SCHEMA 0x0100 /* is show columns query */
2738 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_MERGE_QUERY 0x0200 /* is a query of a merge stmt */
2739 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_LIST_PUSHER 0x0400 /* dummy subquery that pushes a list file descriptor to be used at
2740  * server as its own result */
2741 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_NO_STRICT_OID_CHECK 0x0800 /* normally, only OIDs of updatable views are allowed in parse
2742  * trees; however, for MERGE and UPDATE we sometimes want to
2743  * allow OIDs of partially updatable views */
2744 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_IS_UPD_DEL_QUERY 0x1000 /* set if select was built for an UPDATE or DELETE statement */
2745 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_FOR_UPDATE 0x2000 /* FOR UPDATE clause is active */
2746 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_DISABLE_LOOSE_SCAN 0x4000 /* loose scan not possible on query */
2747 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_MVCC_LOCK_NEEDED 0x8000 /* lock returned rows */
2748 #define PT_SELECT_INFO_READ_ONLY 0x010000 /* read-only system generated queries like show statement */

2769  * assignment reevaluation in MVCC */

2795  } q;

3617 /* Collation coercibility levels associated with parse tree nodes */
3618 enum pt_coll_coerc_lev
3619 {
3620  PT_COLLATION_L0_COERC = 0, /* expressions with COLLATE modifier */
3621  /* Columns */
3622  PT_COLLATION_L1_COERC, /* non-binary collations */
3623  PT_COLLATION_L1_ISO_BIN_COERC, /* with ISO binary coll */
3624  PT_COLLATION_L1_BIN_COERC, /* with binary collation */
3625  /* SELECT values, expressions */
3626  PT_COLLATION_L2_COERC, /* non-binary collations */
3627  PT_COLLATION_L2_BINARY_COERC, /* with binary collation */
3628  PT_COLLATION_L2_BIN_COERC, /* with ISO, UTF8 or EUCKR binary collation */
3629  /* special operators (USER()) */
3630  PT_COLLATION_L3_COERC,
3631  /* constants (string literals) */
3632  PT_COLLATION_L4_COERC, /* non-binary collations */
3633  PT_COLLATION_L4_BINARY_COERC, /* with binary collation */
3634  PT_COLLATION_L4_BIN_COERC, /* with ISO, UTF8 or EUCKR binary collation */
3635  /* HV, session variables */
3636  PT_COLLATION_L5_COERC,
3637  /* nodes not having collation (internal use) */
3638  PT_COLLATION_L6_COERC,
3639 
3640  PT_COLLATION_NOT_APPLICABLE = PT_COLLATION_L6_COERC,
3641  PT_COLLATION_NOT_COERC = PT_COLLATION_L0_COERC,
3642  PT_COLLATION_FULLY_COERC = PT_COLLATION_L5_COERC
3643 };
3644 typedef enum pt_coll_coerc_lev PT_COLL_COERC_LEV;

3647 struct pt_coll_infer
3648 {
